props.active: Controls the **active** state of the item. This is typically used to highlight the component
props.color: Applies specified color to the control when in an **active** state or **input-value** is **true** - supports utility colors (for example `success` or `purple`) or css color (for example `success` or `purple`) or css color (`#033` or `rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5)`). Find a list of built-in classes on the [colors page](/styles/colors#material-colors)
props.contained: Changes the component style by changing how color is applied to the background.
props.title: Generates a `v-list-item-title` component with the supplied value
